import React from 'react';
import { MDBCard, MDBCardBody, MDBCardTitle, MDBCardText, MDBCardImage, MDBBtn, MDBIcon, MDBBtnGroup } from 'mdb-react-ui-kit';

export default function App() {
  return (
    <MDBCard style={{ maxWidth: '100vw' }}>
      <MDBCardImage src='https://mdbcdn.b-cdn.net/img/new/standard/nature/184.webp' position='top' alt='Fissure in Sandstone' />
      <MDBCardBody>
        <MDBBtnGroup className='shadow-0 w-100'>
          <MDBBtn floating tag='a' className='mx-2 bg-white'>
            <MDBIcon fas icon="heart" />
          </MDBBtn>
          <MDBBtn floating tag='a' className='mx-2'>
            <MDBIcon far icon="comment" />
          </MDBBtn>
          <MDBBtn floating tag='a' className='mx-2'>
            <MDBIcon far icon="paper-plane" />
          </MDBBtn>
          <MDBBtn floating tag='a' className='mx-2'>
            <MDBIcon far icon="file" />
          </MDBBtn>
        </MDBBtnGroup>
        <MDBCardTitle>Card title</MDBCardTitle>
        <MDBCardText>
          Some quick example text to build on the card title and make up the bulk of the card's content.
        </MDBCardText>
        <MDBBtn href='#'>Button</MDBBtn>
      </MDBCardBody>
    </MDBCard>
  );
}
